      • generateId

        public String generateId(String key)
        Generates an ID using a simple incrementing system.
        Specified by:
        generateId in interface ProcessContext<T>
        Parameters:
        key - the root string for the incrementing system. Allows for multiple incrementing values, for example task1, task2, task2 as well as fork1, fork2 and fork3. To create a single incrementing system, use "" as the key, this will return a simple sequence of 1, 2, 3, etc. Note: this is not threadsafe -- we assume the graph is being built by a single thread.
